node.text:
@dr.zelana suggests doing these things every day to improve your emotional well-being: 

1. Start your day with water before all else
2. Step outside for fresh air daily
3. Eat sitting down 
4. Connect with a friend
5. Create a consistent bedtime ritual 

Will you be incorporating these practices into your day? Let me know in the comments.

I met so many incredible people at the UPMC/@mageewomens Race to Beat Women’s Cancers yesterday. I want to highlight one woman’s story in particular: Barbara was watching an episode of #TheDrOzShow that talked about the warning signs of pancreatic cancer; after noticing her signs matched, she pushed doctors to evaluate her and run tests. They confirmed she did in fact have pancreatic cancer; and today, I’m proud to learn she is a survivor. #RBWC21 
.
.
.
#Health #cancerawareness #PancreaticCancer #Survivor
